    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Mavroyeni Bey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 52.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the honor to receive in due course your
                    note of the 17th instant, communicating to me the gratifying intelligence
                    conveyed to you by a telegram received by you on that day from the Sublime
                    Porte, that the security of missionaries is completely assured, and that all
                    reports to the contrary are to be denied.</p>
                <p>The information you conveyed was coincident with reports from the United States
                    minister at Constantinople of the sacking and destruction of the buildings of
                    the American mission station at Harpoot, in connection with an appalling
                    massacre of native Christians, and I wish to know whether your telegraphic
                    advices convey authentic information as to those occurrences.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
